data.description: A magnificent one-of-a-kind compound! Gorgeous Victorian home tucked away in desirable Piermont with an income producing carriage house! WELCOME TO "VICTORIAN VIEWS"! RENOVATED 1867 VICTORIAN WITH GORGEOUS RIVER VIEWS! Newly renovated sprinkled with original historic charm throughout. Main home consists of three-level living with 3 bedrooms, 2.5 baths and river views from every room! This distinctive period home boasts opulence through its incredible architecture and unique details. Featuring stunning original wide wood plank floors, stained glass, deep archway windows and a magnificent hand-carved ornate winding staircases - a masterpiece that is rare to find or duplicate.  "Victorian Views" has witnessed the never ending changes of history over 150+ years, and has stood like a fortress through the tests of time. Enjoy tranquility and privacy amidst an exceptional setting, lush and serene timed garden filled with an abundance of various flowers blooming, birds chirping and brilliant butterflies fluttering - a truly magical setting. This impressive home has an abundance of entertaining space inside as well as outside including a wrap-around brick patio perfect for dining al fresco or summer barbecues. Stunning eat-in-kitchen features a custom island centerpiece, top of the line stainless steel appliances & unique built-ins. Elegant dining room and sitting room with original revived tin ceilings and a charming built in window seat. Spacious grand living room beaming with natural light and soaring ceilings. Access through double french doors leading outside to the patio where you can relax in the evening and gaze out at the full moon dancing above the bridge, or enjoy a peaceful morning coffee with the sun rising over the horizon. Large parking area that will fit 4 +cars comfortably. Dry shed for extra storage.   *****  CARRIAGE HOUSE feels like a completely separate residence - perfect for short or long term rental income, guest quarters or extended living. With almost 1,000 sq ft of living space with a full kitchen, 2 full baths, living room dining area, patio, full second floor bedroom loft with private laundry, balcony with river views and private 2-car parking. Discover the magic that living in Piermont has to offer - within minutes to the village center filled with rich history, architecture and beautiful landscapes as well as award winning restaurants, galleries, boutiques & farmers markets! Only 20 minutes to GWB! If you love being outdoors you will enjoy the historic Piermont Pier, Old Erie Path or Tallman Mountain State Park which includes a pool club! Your enchanting private Piermont paradise awaits you!
